cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.IR 

This paper deals with image set clustering and object classification, which are primarily computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also extensively uses deep learning techniques, which makes cs.LG (Machine Learning) another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses unsupervised learning, which falls under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also validates its approach on a robotic application, which makes cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper uses clustering algorithms, which is a subfield of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
